<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="980" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d980">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14076.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Provisional President announces publicly today that he has had a very
                            satisfactory interview with General Villa and that the general will
                            remain in this city indefinitely. He has taken a house here. It is again
                            published that satisfactory arrangements have been made with the troops
                            north of San Luis Potosí.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>